North Korea seals off border town after suspected corona case
North Korea has so far seen its own measures to ward off the coronavirus as a "shining success.".
The country is now reporting a suspected case for the first time.
Due to a first official case of suspected corona in the country, North Korea has completely sealed off a major city for fear of a catastrophe.
Despite the strictest epidemiological defenses in the past six months, "the malignant virus may have been introduced into the country," the state media reported.
A state of emergency has been declared for the region around the border town of Kaesong.
The Communist leadership declared the highest level of alert.
If the suspected case is confirmed, it would be the first official case of infection with Sars-CoV-2 in the isolated country.
North Korea said it had not registered a single infection and described its defenses as a "shining success.".
The information was doubted abroad.
Symptoms of the disease were reportedly detected in a "runaway" who illegally crossed the military demarcation line between South and North Korea on July 19.
The person defected to South Korea three years ago and has now returned across the border.
Initially, there was no confirmation from South Korea of the border crossing within the four-kilometer-wide and largely still-mined military buffer zone.
South Korea's military, however, acknowledged the possibility of an illegal border crossing into North Korea as high, according to reports by the national news agency Yonhap.
Investigations were underway on some people.
North Korea said it called an emergency meeting of the Labor Party's Politburo, chaired by leader Kim Jong Un, on Saturday over the suspected case.
The "dangerous situation in Kaesong could trigger a deadly and destructive disaster.".
As a preventive measure, Kim had already ordered on Friday to "completely blockade Kaesong and isolate every district and the region from others," it added.
The person concerned and all people in Kaesong who had contact with her were quarantined.
The party's central military commission is to investigate the "runaway case" as well as the conduct of the responsible military unit and, if necessary, impose severe punishment.
An estimated 300,000 people live in Kaesong.
Tension ahead of council meeting: City-East and noise protection to be discussed before big summer break
"In addition to environmental issues, the committee members will also vote on the development plan for the major city centre development east project," reads rather casually in the middle section of the municipal press release for the next municipal council meeting on Tuesday, 28 July, at 4.30 p.m. in the Great Hall of the CongressCentrum Pforzheim.
Above all, the revaluation of the eastern city is controversial until the end.
The majorities for this are narrow, most recently in individual committees, depending on their attendance, even negative.
An appeal from the economy (construction, real estate, trade and IT) not to let the project, developed by the citizens and then by the administration and the municipal council, now fail after almost ten years of preparation, criticized project opponent Reinhard Klein as "extra-parliamentary opposition," "clueless," "speculation," "denigration" and "deliberate false statements.".
"Everyone thinks they know better," says Klein, who has been a member of the municipal council for a year as the only representative of the Pforzheim citizens' list.
In fact, after reading the contracts, he is in this position: "I know what I am talking about.".
Contrary to statements by the city administration, the Technical Town Hall is to be redeveloped for 8.5 million euros after subsidies, of which Klein is convinced that it exists.
The city will develop very differently than predicted by the town hall and by the supporters from the business community.
Shaping the city by his own efforts and not by an investor: This is his plan B. One day after Klein, the FDP / FW / UB / LED faction, which also rejects the project, presented an alternative concept.
Essentially, it also provides for the redevelopment of the Technical Town Hall, keeping the Schloßberg open, renting the Ex-Thale for administrative space and a smaller-scale redesign of the city centre, ideally with local authorities.
Environmental issues play a central role
Environmental issues will also play a central role.
Among other things, the municipal council will vote on the noise action plan.
This includes various measures to protect the population of Pforzheim from noise pollution caused by road traffic, including speed reductions in many cases.
In a press release, the local transport club Germany welcomes the widespread introduction of Tempo 30. However, the political leaders in the city are not innocent of the fact that this has to happen, because they have contributed to the massive increase in car traffic and thus noise by neglecting the regular bus service with thinned out clocks and by little commitment to bicycle traffic, according to the VCD.
The municipal council also votes on the city's participation in the Energy and Climate Protection Agency Pforzheim / Enzkreis.
In addition, the agenda includes the accession to the Climate Protection Pact of the State of Baden-Württemberg, the reassessment of parental contributions in the municipal day care centers and the application for admission to the federal smart city funding.
Citizens are welcome, but must heed corona protection measures.
Tim Zimmermann starts the new season with much delay
With a delay of almost half a year, Tim Zimmermann will start his debut season in the ADAC GT Masters on 31 July.
Before the league of supercars can start regular operation, the first test drives were now due.
For Zimmermann, it was all about getting to know his Lamborghini Huracan GT3 better.
For a long time, the Corona crisis prevented Tim Zimmermann from taking his first business trip in the new Lamborghini Huracan of Grasser Racing.
This was now possible under special hygiene conditions.
The 23-year-old from Langenargen completed his first laps at the Lausitzring and was able to get used to his debut in the GT3 car.
"There are already a few things that are different from the Porsche from the previous season," says Zimmermann.
"With the ABS, for example, you have to go into corners differently.
But it was really a lot of fun. ".
Zimmermann also had fun with Steijn Schothorst, with whom he will share his orange sports car in the GT Masters.
Despite his only 25 years, the Dutchman is already experienced in GT racing and was able to help his new team-mate in many ways.
"I'm not a beginner in motorsport, but every new series brings new challenges," says Zimmermann.
"Steijn and I get along brilliantly and we have also made enormous progress from session to session at the Lausitzring.".
Right there - at the Lausitzring - the GT Masters will also hold its first race.
From 31 July, the 33 supercars will race through Lusatia.
But Zimmermann, who is one of 15 series newcomers, knows the track.
In 2015, he was a guest at the Motodrom.
"It worked quickly and I didn't have to get used to the track," says Zimmermann, who is competing for the Friedrichshafen-based racing community Graf Zeppelin.
"The Lausitzring has many fast passages that you have to hit optimally in order to be fast.".
How fast Zimmermann really is will be revealed in two weeks.
"Of course, the teams play a bit of poker in the tests," he says.
"Ultimately, however, we are very satisfied and are looking forward to the first weekend at the Lausitzring.".
The race in Brandenburg will be the start of a packed calendar.
There are seven races scheduled until the beginning of November.
The current situation is that no spectators will be allowed - but there is a celebrity guest.
In mid-August at the Nürburgring, ex-Formula 1 driver Niko Hülkenberg will take the GT wheel.
British transport minister caught cold by quarantine decision
The British government's decision to quarantine holidaymakers in Spain for two weeks after their return has caught the country's transport minister cold, according to press reports.
Grant Shapps is currently on holiday in Spain, of all places, while his colleagues at home decided on the measure on Saturday.
Due to the rising corona numbers in Spain, the cabinet in London removed the country from the list of countries from which entry without quarantine conditions is possible.
The new rule will apply from today, Sunday, so Shapps will also have to quarantine after his return.
In Austria, the government has also imposed quarantine measures for returnees.
But the scheme will only apply to those who are just on holiday from Saturday, August 1, and has not been introduced overnight.
Incidentally, Spain is still considered one of the "safe countries" in Austria for which no quarantine is required in Austria.
"Many ministers must have known in advance that there was a possibility of a quarantine being imposed on holidaymakers in Spain," commented Labour MP Diane Abbot.
"But apparently no one bothered to tell Grant Shapps.".
Less than a month after the end of the corona emergency in Spain and the expiry of the strict curfew, the number of infections in the country is rising again.
Virologists blame nightlife in particular for the recent spread.
Spain is one of Britain's favourite holiday destinations.
The British government currently advises against unnecessary travel to the Spanish mainland, with the exception of the Canary and Balearic Islands, which are particularly popular with British holidaymakers.
To date, more than 272,000 infections with the novel coronavirus and more than 28,000 deaths have been recorded in Spain.
Russia: Navy Day: Putin announces hypersonic weapons for warships
Russian President Vladimir Putin has announced that his country's warships will be equipped with the latest hypersonic weapons on the occasion of Navy Day.
With these weapons, which are unique in the world, the combat capabilities of the Russian naval forces would be extended, Putin said on Sunday in St. Petersburg at the central naval parade.
According to the Interfax agency, the Ministry of Defense also informed about successful tests of the Zircon hypersonic missile built for the Navy.
The hypersonic weapons have a multiple of the speed of sound of around 343 metres per second.
They are considered weapons of the future.
Underwater Tropedeo to be built
Construction will also continue on the atomically equipped underwater torpedo Poseidon, it said.
The planned sea drone is planned to destroy coastal targets.
The president, who himself also sailed a military boat, said that this year alone 40 new ships would be put into service with the individual naval units of the largest country in the world.
Russia has such a large coastal area as no other country in the world.
For 300 years, the navy has reliably protected Russia, Putin said on the day celebrated by sailors nationwide.
Naval forces also celebrated Navy Day with parades in many other Russian coastal towns.
In Syria, where Russia is fighting alongside ruler Bashar al-Assad, the military demonstrated strength at a weapons show in the Mediterranean port of Tartus.
Ammunition was also fired there.
A video released by the Ministry of Defense showed not only warships, including a submarine, but also attack helicopters and jets.
Hurricane "Hanna" reaches Texas: Help hampered by Corona
Washington - The first hurricane of this year's season over the Atlantic has made landfall in Texas.
Life-threatening flooding, strong winds and heavy rains are now threatening parts of the US state, announced the National Hurricane Center of the US climate agency NOAA in the night to Sunday (local time).
Governor Greg Abbott declared a state of emergency for many districts.
The corona pandemic raging in Texas is complicating the work of aid workers, Abbott said, according to US media.
Evacuees called for caution
"Every hurricane is a huge challenge," Abbott said, according to the Houston Chronicle.
Referring to the hurricane in Texas, he added, "This challenge is complicated and compounded by the fact that it is sweeping through what is the most COVID-19-affected area of the state.".
According to Johns Hopkins University, around 5,000 people have died as a result of the corona pandemic in Texas alone.
Abbott called on people who had to leave their homes to exercise caution.
They should not disregard practices "that we have become accustomed to," such as wearing masks, the governor said, according to CBS.
It was important that everyone kept their distance.
Therefore, hotel rooms have been provided in some places.
In addition, Corona should be tested in emergency shelters.
Damage was initially reported only from the coastal town of Port Mansfield.
Storm warning withdrawn
With wind speeds of up to 150 kilometers per hour, "Hanna" hit the island of Padre Island just off the Texas coast, according to authorities.
The tropical storm had previously been upgraded to the lowest level one hurricane.
A storm surge warning was initially issued for the coastal section from Port Mansfield to Sargent and was later withdrawn.
Authorities expected a slowdown as "Hanna" moved further inland and headed for northeastern Mexico.
"Douglas" is moving towards Hawaii
In the Pacific, hurricane "Douglas" was on its way towards Hawaii during the night to Sunday with wind speeds of around 150 kilometers per hour.
The hurricane center, however, expected it to weaken further.
According to the forecast, it should be near the largest islands of Hawaii on Sunday (local time) - then as a storm just below the hurricane threshold.
Over the Atlantic, NOAA expected an above-average active hurricane season this year, according to a May forecast.
From June to the end of November, up to ten hurricanes are expected, of which up to six could become very strong hurricanes, the authority had said.
On average, there are six hurricanes per year over the Atlantic, three of which develop into major storms.
In view of available climate data and the higher water temperatures in the Atlantic and the Caribbean, the probability of a normal season is only 30 percent, the probability of a below-average season is only ten percent, it was said at the time.
US President Donald Trump wrote via Twitter that his administration is closely monitoring the storms and is in contact with the affected states.
